This feature allows to manually define the data structure required for the CSV Reader component to read the incoming CSV files.

> Warning

The configured data structure must match the structure of the incoming CSV files, including the order of the fields.

## Creating a new CSV data structure
- Open the CSV Reader resource in the configuration editor as described in [Configuring DT3 Project Resources](/doxee-platform/docs/configuring-dt3-project-resources).

-  If no data fields have been created yet, click **ADD**.![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

- Enter the required parameters:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Field**

**Description**

**Name**

Enter the name of the data field.

**Position**

*(optional) *Set the position of the data field within the structure.

**Default value**

*(optional) *Enter the default value of the field.

**Set as optional**

Select this option to indicate that the field is optional.

**Add another**

Select this option if you want to add another field after this one, without going back to the main screen.

- Click **ADD FIELD **to confirm.

> Tip

To create additional fields, see Adding a field below.

> Note

For more information on how to import an existing CSV structure, see: [DT3 CSV Reader - Global Actions](/doxee-platform/docs/2-dt3-csv-reader-global-actions).

## Managing the CSV data structure
![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

### Available actions
**Icon**

**Action**

**Description**

![](data:image/png;base64,)

[**Add**](#_bookmark26)

Add a new field to the data structure.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Delete**

Permanently delete a field from the data structure.

The system displays a confirmation dialog before proceeding:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

> Warning

This action cannot be undone.

-

**Add fields to HEADER**

**element**

Select this option if you want to add these fields to the HEADER element (in addition to the DOCUMENT element) that will be visible in the Mapper UI.

> Important

This option is selected by default and cannot be disabled if the data structure was imported via an existing CSV file.

### **Adding a field**
- Click  ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Add**).

- Enter the required parameters; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Field**

**Description**

**Name**

Enter the name of the data field.

**Position**

*(optional) *Set the position of the data field within the structure.

**Default value**

*(optional) *Enter the default value of the field.

**Set as optional**

Select this option to indicate that the field is optional.

**Add another**

Select this option if you want to add another field after this one, without going back to the main screen.

- Click **ADD FIELD **to confirm. The new field is listed in the main table.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

### Editing a field
To edit an existing field, move your mouse over the corresponding row and clicking on the parameter that you want to edit; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Tip

To change the position of a field in the data structure, click on the  ![](data:image/png;base64,)  icon in the corresponding row and drag the field to the required position; for example:
